  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`): 1.5.2\r\n\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- **Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: AWS\r\n- **OS** (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Debian GNU/Linux 8 (jessie)\r\n- **Kernel** (e.g. `uname -a`): 4.4.41-k8s\r\n- **Install tools**: Kops 1.5\r\n- **Others**: Terraform\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**: We had someone install and remove this chart a few times: https://github.com/kubernetes/charts/tree/master/stable/concourse, they deleted the PVCs as documented but this left the PVs in `Released` state and then looped calling `VolumeDelete` and getting `VolumeInUse` with no back-off.\r\n\r\nThis resulted in ~50k AWS API calls over 24 hours.\r\n\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**: At the very least the calls should have backed-off on failure.\r\n\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it** (as minimally and precisely as possible): Delete a PVC for a StatelfulSet without deleting the PV.\r\n\r\ncc: @chrislovecnm & @jingxu97 ",
